## R2 — Competitor landscape (RESOLVED)

### Amarillo-based competitors (all ranking above Dimitroff regionally)
| Competitor | Est. | City pages? | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Overhead Door Co. of Amarillo | 1968 | None | Strongest brand; no local LP strategy |
| Price Overhead Door | 1971 | None | Legacy player; static site |
| Willow Creek Overhead Door | 2000 | None | Family-owned, Amarillo |
| Integrity Overhead Door | ~2010 | Limited service-area pages | Closest to an LP strategy |
| Dockins Overhead Doors | Unknown | None | Supplier + installer |
| A&H Overhead Door, Hollis, A-1 | Unknown | None | Smaller locals |

### NE New Mexico competitors (thin coverage)
- **TRU Garage Door** — Clovis, NM (30+ yrs combined exp, primary Clovis competitor)
- **CMB Garage Doors** — Lubbock/Clovis/Cave Creek footprint

### Key gap: NO Amarillo-based competitor has dedicated landing pages for smaller Panhandle towns (Pampa, Borger, Perryton, Dalhart, Hereford, Canyon, Friona) or NE NM cities. This is Dimitroff's primary SEO opportunity — rank for "garage door repair [small city]" where Amarillo competitors have zero local signals.

### Content angle for Dimitroff:
- Local Dumas/Moore County authority vs. "big city company that drives out"
- Bilingual service ("Se Habla Español") targets Hispanic community across Panhandle
- Commercial + dock equipment differentiates from residential-only competitors
- Speed (same-day, 48-hr) as primary conversion hook

