## R3 — SEO Analyzer app architecture (HARD BLOCKER — RESOLVED)

**Front-end:** https://mwegter95.github.io/free-seo-analyzer-with-js-rendering/ (GH Pages static app)
**Back-end:** `api.michaelwegter.com` — the existing Flask backend (server.py), NOT a separate service

### Routes (all require JWT auth via existing `require_auth`):
- `POST /seo/analyze` — single-page analysis
- `POST /seo/prescan` — pre-scan step
- `POST /seo/crawl` — full site crawl
- `GET /seo/crawl/stream` — SSE stream for crawl progress
- `GET /seo/reports` — list user's saved reports
- `GET /seo/reports/<filename>` — fetch a saved report

### Auth flow:
- Uses **the same JWT auth system** as the rest of mw-backend (`/register`, `/login`)
- Users can register with any fake email + password; passwords hashed with bcrypt; reports stored per-user at `data/seo_reports/<user_id>/`
- Front-end CORS already allows `http://localhost:5015` and the GH Pages origin

### Demo-builder instruction (CRITICAL):
**Do NOT rebuild the SEO analyzer.** It already exists and works. The WP demo should include a "Free SEO Analysis" section/page with a CTA button that links to `https://mwegter95.github.io/free-seo-analyzer-with-js-rendering/` (opens in new tab or embeds as iframe). This lets the proposal reviewer register with a fake email, log in, run an analysis on dimitroffdoorrepair.com (or any URL), and see the real analyzer — zero build effort, maximum demo impact.

The analyzer CORS list already includes the relevant origins so no backend changes are needed.

