## Additional findings (planner should incorporate)

### Schema markup priority
- `LocalBusiness` + `HomeAndConstructionBusiness` schema on every page
- `Service` schema on each service page with `areaServed` listing target cities
- `FAQPage` schema on service pages (common Q: "Do you serve [city]?")
- `BreadcrumbList` on all city LPs

### Core Web Vitals for WordPress
- Use GeneratePress or Blocksy theme (lightweight, ~30kb CSS base)
- Implement WP Rocket or LiteSpeed Cache for caching
- Serve images as WebP; lazy-load below fold
- Avoid page builders (Elementor bloat) — build with Gutenberg blocks + custom CSS

### Conversion optimization
- Sticky click-to-call button on mobile (most garage door leads are phone calls)
- Above-fold CTA: "Call Now" + "Request Estimate" on every page
- Trust bar: BBB badge, "Se Habla Español", "Same-Day Service", "90-Day Warranty"

### WordPress demo specifics
- Port 8090 (as per plan), WP + MySQL in Docker on Surface
- Bridge blueprint: clone `maryland_driveway_wp_bridge_blueprint.py` pattern
- Demo admin credentials to document for live test

